What you need to know:  Nigeria became a modern state in 1914 when British colonial powers amalgamated the northern and southern protectorates into one unit.For the first 22 years there was a foggy or unclear direction in the emergence of popular music practices in urban Nigeria.The next 24 years saw interaction and budding among Nigerians as a new sociopolitical order emerged from the ashes of the Second World War.The liberal period marked the most diverse and expansive moment of popular music practices in Nigeria so far